          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "The Chief Technology Officer (CTO) in PERA is responsible for providing technical leadership to the IT & Communications team. The CTO assists the Director General in ensuring IT-enabled solutions for all PERA functions, including digitization of processes at Headquarters and Enforcement Stations. Key responsibilities include leading the IT & Communication Wing, overseeing software development and deployment, monitoring technology trends, managing IT infrastructure, ensuring data and cyber security, developing information security frameworks, and managing MIS & GIS functions. The CTO reports to the Director General of PERA and is appointed by the Director General on the recommendations of the Contractual Employment Committee. The position requires a master's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or Information Technology with significant post-qualification experience, including public sector experience.",
