                "text": "Position Title: Deputy Director (Implementation) Reports to: Additional Director General (Monitoring & Implementation) Purpose of the Position:\nThe Deputy Director (Implementation) shall be responsible for ensuring the effective enforcement of PERA’s mandate across the province, maintaining operational transparency, and overseeing all field activities of the Enforcement Squad. The incumbent will c oordinate the implementation of directives issued by the Authority, supervise recruitment, postings, transfers, contract renewals, terminations, performance appraisals, and disciplinary actions related to Enforcement Officers, System Support Officers, and Investigation Officers. All intelligence and inspection reports concerning enforcement operations shall be routed through the Deputy Director to ensure integrity, accountability, and uniform application of PERA’s enforcement standards. Areas of Responsibilities:\n\n• Execute and supervise enforcement activities as per PERA’s mandate and directives issued by the\nDirector General.\n• Ensure uniform compliance with enforcement procedures, field inspection protocols, and transparency\nmechanisms.\n• Monitor and evaluate implementation progress, identifying operational bottlenecks and proposing\ncorrective measures.\n• Oversee recruitment processes for Enforcement Station staff , ensuring merit, transparency, and\nadherence to PERA’s recruitment policy.\n• Administer contract renewals, extensions, postings, and transfers of System Support Officers in\ncoordination with the Admin & HR Wing.\n• Recommend disciplinary action, termination, or contract non -renewal in cases of misconduct,\nnegligence, or poor performance.\n• Supervise and review annual performance appraisals of enforcement staff, ensuring objective evaluation\nand linkage with renewal, promotion, or disciplinary decisions.\n• Maintain performance dashboards and records for all field officers to enable data-driven accountability.\n• Receive, analyse, and consolidate all intelligence reports from the Enforcement and Investigation units.\n• Initiate inquiries or fact-finding proceedings against officers under suspicion of corruption, malpractice,\nor dereliction of duty.\n• Ensure all intelligence inputs are confidentially handled and submitted to the ADG for final review and\naction.\n• Develop intelligence-gathering mechanisms to pre-empt violations of PERA’s regulatory framework.\n• Maintain a transparent record of enforcement actions, officer conduct, and administrative decisions.\n• Submit periodic performance and intelligence summaries to the Director and recommend policy -level\nimprovements for systemic efficiency.\n• Serve as the focal officer for field data validation and verification of enforcement outcomes.\n• Exercise direct administrative and functional control over the Intelligence Wing to ensure effective\ncollection, collation, and analysis of field intelligence related to enforcement, compliance, and emerging regulatory risks.\n\n• Oversee systematic intelligence gathering from Enforcement Stations and external sources, ensuring\nverification and classification of actionable information.\n• Maintain close coordination with Chairperson/ Secretary DERB, field units, and relevant enforcement or\nsecurity agencies for intelligence sharing, joint operations, and preventive interventions.\n• Prepare and submit confidential intelligence briefs, risk assessments, and analytical reports to the\nDirector (Implementation) and Director General for policy and operational decision-making.\n• Ensure strict confidentiality, secure record-keeping, and controlled dissemination of intelligence data in\naccordance with official secrecy and regulatory protocols. Competencies & Personal Attributes:\n• Relationship management & Communication Skills.\n• Analytical skills.\n• Should be proficient in the use of IT\n• Understanding of Financial Rules of Government of Punjab and PERA’s financial regulations\n• Risk management skills\n• Financial reporting skills",
